709505f-a.text:
Sixth Ave., north from West 43rd Street to Central Park, and showing a general view northeast from the Bush Terminal Building (130 West 42nd Street, south side, between Sixth Ave. and Broadway). This view taken prior to the sudden building boom shows the Plaza Hotel, the Sherry Netherland, the Ritz Tower, St, Patrick's Cathedral, the Collegiate Church of St. Nicholas and B.F. Keith's Hippodrome (Sixth Ave., east side, between West 43rd and 44th Streets). Also shown are the Queensboro and the Hellgate R.R. Bridges.
May 1926.
Brown Brothers.

713151f-b.text:
W 43rd Street, west from and across Sixth Avenue, as viewed from the Aeolian Hall, showing at Times Square the Paramount Building. In the lower right hand corner is the southwesterly corner of the Hippodrome. To the extreme left appears a portion of the Times Building. View No. 2 shows same in the center thereof. Prominently depicted in the latter is also the Bush Terminal Bldg. on 42nd Street. In the background is the North (Hudson) River and the Jersey Shore.

September 14, 1927.
Views 1 and 2

P. L. Sperr

709497f-a.text:
Sixth Avenue, east side, north from W. 43rd to 44th Streets, showing the Hippodrome occupying this frontage. As apparent, this landmark is under demolition and the site will be cleared for use as a parking lot. At the right margin is a portion of the R. C. A. Building.
September 17, 1939
George Jiranek
New York Public Library
Photostat Division

Sixth Avenue, east side, from W. 43rd to 44th Streets, showing the former Hippodrome site. This has been cleared and will be utilized as an automobile parking lot. The photographer is viewing southeastward towards buildings on the north side of

709507f-b.text:
Sixth Avenue, from West 43rd to 44th Streets, showing the low buildings on the west side,as viewed across the former Hippodrome site. The latter has become the parking lot shown. This occupies the easterly frontage of the Avenue. Times Square and Broadway are just beyond, distinguished by the dominant Paramount Building. Vcrious hotels are on the side streets. Observable are the 44th Street HHotel, the Hotel Langwell, the Peerless and the St James.
View 3 is northwestward towards W. 44th Street.
May 5, 1940
Views 1,2,3
P. L. Sperr
